  prototype={<>#define DEBUG&#95;TYPE&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&quot;amdgpu-regbanklegalize&quot;</>}>
Definitions of RegBankLegalize Rules for all opcodes.

Implementation of container for all the Rules and search. Fast search for most common case when Rule.Predicate checks <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/llt">LLT</a> and uniformity of register in operand 0.

<Link id="l00331" /><CodeLine lineNumber="331"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Syntactic sugar wrapper for predicate lambda that enables &#39;&amp;&amp;&#39;, &#39;||&#39; and &#39;!&#39;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00332" /><CodeLine lineNumber="332" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/predicate"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">class </span><span class="doxyHighlight">Predicate &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00333" /><CodeLine lineNumber="333"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">private</span><span class="doxyHighlight">:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00334" /><CodeLine lineNumber="334"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">struct </span><span class="doxyHighlight">Elt &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00335" /><CodeLine lineNumber="335"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Save formula composed of Pred, &#39;&amp;&amp;&#39;, &#39;||&#39; and &#39;!&#39; as a jump table.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00336" /><CodeLine lineNumber="336"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Sink ! to Pred. For example !((A &amp;&amp; !B) || C) -&gt; (!A || B) &amp;&amp; !C</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00337" /><CodeLine lineNumber="337"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Sequences of &amp;&amp; and || will be represented by jumps, for example:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00338" /><CodeLine lineNumber="338"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (A &amp;&amp; B &amp;&amp; ... X) or (A &amp;&amp; B &amp;&amp; ... X) || Y</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00339" /><CodeLine lineNumber="339"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A == true jump to B</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00340" /><CodeLine lineNumber="340"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A == false jump to end or Y, result is A(false) or Y</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00341" /><CodeLine lineNumber="341"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// (A || B || ... X) or (A || B || ... X) &amp;&amp; Y</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00342" /><CodeLine lineNumber="342"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A == true jump to end or Y, result is A(true) or Y</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00343" /><CodeLine lineNumber="343"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A == false jump to B</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="344"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Notice that when negating expression, we simply flip Neg on each Pred</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="345"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and swap TJumpOffset and FJumpOffset (&amp;&amp; becomes ||, || becomes &amp;&amp;).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="346"><span class="doxyHighlight">    std::function&lt;bool(</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineinstr">MachineInstr</a> &amp;)&gt; Pred;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="347"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> Neg; </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Neg of Pred is calculated before jump</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="348"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">unsigned</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> TJumpOffset;</span></CodeLine>
